The paper deals with coding theory and information theory, which are typically categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the study of error-correcting codes, which can be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of Augustin's method and Gallager's inner bound suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves the study of probability and statistics, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
